title: The Eagles - 1972-06-14 Fair Grounds Oklahoma City OK
description:
In memory of Glenn Frey. Here is another nice Eagles bootleg.

Please enjoy, share with friends and please seed :)

THE EAGLES
FAIR GROUNDS PAVILION
OKLAHOMA CITY, OK (USA)
JUNE 14, 1972
FROM THE KRW_CO COLLECTION

AUDIENCE ANALOG MASTER to DAT to CDR2 to EAC SECURE MODE to FLAC LEVEL 8

THE BAND
Glenn Frey  vocals guitars slide guitar
Don Henley  vocals drums
Bernie Leadon  vocals guitars banjo
Randy Meisner  vocals bass

SET LIST
1 Take it Easy (fade in)
2 Witchy Woman
3 Train Leaves Here This Morning
4 Peaceful Easy Feeling
5 How Long
6 Get Up Baby
7 Nightingale
8 Earlybird

Recorded using a Lloyds cassette recorder boombox with two unknown ceramic omni directional mics.

Recorded onto a Sony UHF C90 cassette.

Received in trade in 2004. Thank you to the taper for making this available.

PLEASE DONT POST THIS ON ANY OTHER TRACKERS.
AND PLEASE DONT ALTER THIS RECORDING IN ANY WAY.
THANK YOU,AS ALWAYS ENJOY.CHEERS KRW_CO
